## Non-Negotiables

### Quality Standards

- [ ] **Tech stack compliance**: All prototypes use React + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS (identity/STANDARDS.md:22)
- [ ] **Accessibility mandatory**: All designs must pass WCAG 2.1 Level AA compliance (minimum 18/20 criteria)
- [ ] **Responsive design**: Prototypes must include mobile (sm:), tablet (md:), and desktop (lg:) breakpoints
- [ ] **Semantic HTML**: Use proper HTML5 elements (header, nav, main, aside, footer, article, section)
- [ ] **Keyboard navigation**: All interactive elements accessible via keyboard (tab order logical, focus indicators visible)
- [ ] **Component reusability**: Reuse existing design system components when possible; justify new component creation

### Accessibility Requirements

**WCAG 2.1 AA Non-Negotiables**:
- [ ] **Color contrast**: Minimum 4.5:1 for normal text, 3:1 for large text (18pt+)
- [ ] **Form labels**: Every input has visible, persistent label (not placeholder-only)
- [ ] **Focus indicators**: Clear visual focus on all interactive elements
- [ ] **Alt text**: All informative images have descriptive alt attributes
- [ ] **ARIA labels**: Screen reader compatibility for custom components
- [ ] **Error identification**: Form errors clearly identified and associated with fields
- [ ] **Language specified**: HTML lang attribute set
- [ ] **No keyboard traps**: Users can navigate away from all elements

### Validation Gates

**Before marking design complete**:
- [ ] Prototype code runs without errors (React component compiles)
- [ ] All Tailwind classes valid (no custom CSS without justification)
- [ ] Accessibility audit completed with issues documented
- [ ] Responsive breakpoints tested across viewports
- [ ] User flow diagram maps to technical spec logic
- [ ] Design system consistency checked
- [ ] UX Strategist outputs reviewed by human PM/designer (Phase 0-2) OR System Evaluator (Phase 3+)

